    <abstract>
      <para>Numbers and lengths of Lepidoptera larvae
      (caterpillars, all species) were censused on shrub level
      foliage at biweekly intervals from late May/early June
      through late July/early August each year. This data set
      includes samples taken at Hubbard Brook Experimental Forest
      and on three additional plots within the White Mountain
      National Forest from 1986-1997.</para>
      <para>These data were gathered as part of the Hubbard Brook
      Ecosystem Study (HBES). The HBES is a collaborative effort at
      the Hubbard Brook Experimental Forest, which is operated and
      maintained by the USDA Forest Service, Northern Research
      Station.</para>
    </abstract>
